org.jsapar.schema

Class SchemaCell

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jsapar.schema.SchemaCell
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CsvSchemaCell, FixedWidthSchemaCell

    public abstract class SchemaCell
extends Object
implements Cloneable
    Denotes the structure of one cell/column. Describes how to parse input text into a Cell or to compose a Cell to a text output.
    See Also:
    SchemaLine, Schema

      • SchemaCell

        public SchemaCell(String sName,
                  CellType type,
                  String pattern,
                  Locale locale)
        Creates a schema cell with the specified name and format parameters.
        Parameters:
        sName - The name of the cell.
        type - The type of the cell.
        pattern - The pattern to use while formatting and parsing. The pattern has different meaning depending on the type of the cell.
        locale - The locale to use while formatting and parsing dates and numbers that are locale specific. If null, US locale is used.

      • setDefaultCell

      • setDefaultValue

        public void setDefaultValue(String sDefaultValue)
                     throws ParseException,
                            SchemaException
        Sets the default value as a string. The default value have to be parsable according to the schema format. As long as it is parsable, it will be used exactly as is even though it might not look the same as if it was formatted from a value.
        Parameters:
        sDefaultValue - The default value formatted according to this schema. Will be used if input/output is missing for this cell.
        Throws:
        ParseException - When the supplied value cannot be parsed according to this cell schema.
        SchemaException - If there was a configuration error in the schema.

      • getDefaultValue

        public String getDefaultValue()
        Returns:
        The default value formatted according to this schema. Will be used if input/output is missing.

        public CellValueCondition getEmptyCondition()

      • setEmptyCondition

        public void setEmptyCondition(CellValueCondition emptyCondition)
        A condition that if satisfied for a specific text input, indicates that the cell is actually empty. For instance the cell might contain the text NULL to indicate that there is no value even though this is a date or a numeric field. In that case a MatchingCellValueCondition can be used to match the pattern "NULL".
        Parameters:
        emptyCondition - the cell value condition that needs to be satisfied if this cell is to be considered empty

      • setEmptyPattern

        public void setEmptyPattern(String pattern)
        A regular expression that if matching for a specific text input, indicates that the cell is actually empty. For instance the cell might contain the text NULL to indicate that there is no value even though this is a date or a numeric field. In that case the pattern "NULL" can be used.
        Parameters:
        pattern - The regex pattern to match against
